The African Development Bank (AfDB) will meet with Nigerian business leaders on Tuesday ahead of this year’s Africa Investment Forum (AIF). The AIF – the continent’s biggest investment marketplace for accelerated economic transformation – is slated for November 11 to 13 in Johannesburg, South Africa. A press release signed by one of the AfDB’s spokespersons, Fatimah Abubakar Alkali, said the meeting which will take place in Transcorp Hilton, Abuja, is aimed at wooing investors ahead of this year’s second AIF. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE It targets chief executive officers, captains of industry, state governments and other key players that will re-affirm Nigeria’s investment-ready status, the release said. The meeting will build on the quantity and quality of deals brokered in 2018, as well as explore investment opportunities across the continent, it added. “By convening Nigeria’s premium project sponsors, borrowers, lenders and investors, the road show will showcase bankable projects, attract financing, and provide platforms for investing across multiple countries”, the AfDB release said. AIF: Partners reaffirm commitment to close Africa’s infrastructure gap Africa Investment Forum Africa Investment Forum strikes $208bn investment deals Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin